reviews.title: Horrible

reviews.title: Great concept bad execution
reviews.comment: This app could be completely useful if it was convenient. The fact that it NEVER remembers my sign in, even though it asks me if it should and I say yes, makes this app tedious and a complete choir to use. It also make me sign in AGAIN to reach specific web pages, linked through the app, to read emails or see specific assignment grades. At this point, I\'m better off going through a web browser for what I need.

reviews.title: meh-I\'ve never felt more neutral about an app
reviews.comment: For my school it doesn\'t have many practical applications (I can\'t speak for others). There are things like grades (final grades only) and schedule, but thats all I could foresee using this for on a cell phone. For library and other options it hyperlinks to a web browser. So, I guess its just not all that practical an app to have.  Would be better with an email option and other every day options (like grades throughout the semester)  On the plus side could be pretty cool for a new student to a school since it has a campus map and a few other things.   Good start, though... fast, responsive...just not very practical for everyday use..maybe once or twice a semester
